page.title: 05WASHINGTON WILDFOWL PARK
page.content: The side pens of Washington Wild Fowl Park hold aggressive birds e.g. Black Swan, Andean and Magellan Geese, Pintails, Wigeons, Shelduck,Whooper and Trumpeter Swans, King Eider, Barow's Golden Eye and Hooded Mergensers. The Wader Lake has hides where you can see Redshank, Dunlin,Snipe, Lapwings, Common Sandpipers and Greenshanks. The Reed Bed Pond hides Sedge Warblers and Reed Buntings. The Hawthorn Wood contains Oak,Elder, Ash and Hawthorn which are cover for Blackbird, Robin, Chaffinch, Blue Tit, Blackcap, Whitethroat and Lesser Whitethroat. Autumn and winter berries attract Redwings, Fieldfare and Goldcrests. An enjoyable and informative place to visit throughout the year.
